txt.en: 'What may I do for you on this day?'
'Yes, I was just torturing this filth who entered Naerband, unbeknownst to me.'
'[placeholder]!'
'A trifling matter.'
'This way!'
'I, I suppose there are more important tasks.'
Instance: Escape From Naerband
'We can escape through this cave.'
'I know you seek more flame wraiths, Urudanî, my gift of flame and fire.'
'Yes, I will put this [placeholder] in a cell and deal with the filth later.'
'You have my devotion, for in Sauron's death, you have come to me.'
'Fire is truly the greatest tool in torment.'
'It seems we must delay our session.'
'How dare you interfere, in my domain!'
'Do not look relieved!'
'Oh what I have in store for you!'
'Now that you are awake, you poor excuse for a [placeholder], I can begin.'
'Where is the enjoyment of torturing, when the victim can not witness the pain?!'
'I shall devise torment in you, unequalled in any of the Ages of the world!'
'Now, Where to begin?!'
'Who there disturbs my session?'
'Ah, Urudanî, You are truly Lord Sauron's gift to Naerband.'
'You embody his masterwork of death and ruin.'
'Yes, Urudanî.'
'[placeholder], I am the warden of Naerband, the greatest of Lord Sauron's prisons.
'You shall never forget that, for you shall never escape!'
